reviewText: Awesome video to make sure you get the most out of your AK visit.

This was great movie!  I have always wanted to visit Alaska!  My Dad lived Anchorage Alaska for A short time as A kid!  In the early 2000'0 my Dad and Granddad visited Denali National Park!  My Grandad passed away in January 2013!  When my Dad got back from taking my Grandad to Alaska my Dad showed me A slide show of his trip!  Since than I have been wanting to visit Alaska!  The places that I would like to fist in Alaska are Denali National Park, the state capital of Alaska Juno, Nome where the famous sled dog race the Iditarad took place, and Homer!  I grew up with this series as A kid!
This was A OK movie!  Seeing the hotels in the park were beautiful!  I grew up with series as A kid!
I have several movies about Alaska but this is the best!  Lorne Greene does an excellent job.  Is this available in DVD format?
